Why this works (the deeper reason)

Human language is underdetermined.

Words don’t contain meaning — they trigger interpretation.

Meaning emerges from:
	•	context
	•	reader assumptions
	•	perspective

So a well-constructed story can behave exactly like your multi-angle drawing.

